Cross-validation results
Accuracy : 0.872848  [good]
F1-score : 0.381215  [weak]
ROC-AUC  : 0.894389  [good]
MSE      : 0.103923  [fair]
R2       : -1.162673  [weak]

Result interpretation
- Accuracy shows overall prediction correctness across all samples.
- F1-score is important here because handover events are less frequent than non-handover events.
- ROC-AUC measures how well the model separates handover from non-handover behavior.
- MSE and R2 are computed from predicted probabilities, giving an additional view of score quality.

Benefits of these results
- Better handover prediction can support earlier cell-switch preparation.
- Earlier preparation can reduce call drops and service interruption.
- Network teams can use the results to identify weak-signal and unstable mobility zones.
- Feature importance helps explain which radio measurements influence decisions most.
- The model is lightweight enough to be useful for real-time telecom and hardware-oriented workflows.

